    "active_lock_reason": null,
    "body": "1. Generate a new addon with ember-cli 3.15.2. \r\n2. In that addon run `ember g component --classic -cc foo`\r\n3. Try to use that component, you'll see \r\n\r\n    > Error: Could not find module `example-addon/templates/components/foo` imported from `example-addon/components/foo`\r\n\r\nThe problem is that the generated hbs file is at `addon/components/foo.hbs`, but the layout import statement in `addon/components/foo.js` tries to import from `../templates/components/foo`.\r\n\r\nI reproduced this bug on both ember-source 3.15 and 3.18.0-canary+f0fceae4. I was unable to reproduce while running `yarn link`ed to ember-source on either of those commits, which suggests there is some possibly-unrelated weirdness in the way the blueprints detect their environment when running symlinked.",
