    "body": "# Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nIn any ember project, paste the following into a template file: \r\n```\r\n<div style={{html-safe concat (\"background-color: \" color.hex)}}></div>\r\n```\r\n[Twiddle](https://ember-twiddle.com/5a588221fdc55d0febd93650eae3a156?openFiles=templates.application%5C.hbs%2C)\r\n\r\n# Expected behavior\r\nEmber tells me that my syntax is invalid, in a proper error message with a line number.\r\n\r\n# Actual behavior\r\nEmber CLI gives the following output:\r\n```\r\n(node:97567) UnhandledPromiseRejectionWarning: TypeError: Cannot read property '0' of undefined\r\n    at isAttrs (/Users/gaelan/src/maps/node_modules/ember-source/dist/ember-template-compiler.js:7104:26)\r\n    at PathExpression (/Users/gaelan/src/maps/node_modules/ember-source/dist/ember-template-compiler.js:7092:15)\r\n    at visitNode (/Users/gaelan/src/maps/node_modules/ember-source/dist/ember-template-compiler.js:5159:16)\r\n    at visitKey (/Users/gaelan/src/maps/node_modules/ember-source/dist/ember-template-compiler.js:5217:20)\r\n    at visitNode (/Users/gaelan/src/maps/node_modules/ember-source/dist/ember-template-compiler.js:5178:9)\r\n    at visitArray (/Users/gaelan/src/maps/node_modules/ember-source/dist/ember-template-compiler.js:5233:20)\r\n    at visitKey (/Users/gaelan/src/maps/node_modules/ember-source/dist/ember-template-compiler.js:5215:7)\r\n    at visitNode (/Users/gaelan/src/maps/node_modules/ember-source/dist/ember-template-compiler.js:5178:9)\r\n    at visitKey (/Users/gaelan/src/maps/node_modules/ember-source/dist/ember-template-compiler.js:5217:20)\r\n    at visitNode (/Users/gaelan/src/maps/node_modules/ember-source/dist/ember-template-compiler.js:5178:9)\r\n(node:97567) UnhandledPromiseRejectionWarning: Unhandled promise rejection. This error originated either by throwing inside of an async function without a catch block, or by rejecting a promise which was not handled with .catch(). To terminate the node process on unhandled promise rejection, use the CLI flag `--unhandled-rejections=strict` (see https://nodejs.org/api/cli.html#cli_unhandled_rejections_mode). (rejection id: 2)\r\n(node:97567) [DEP0018] DeprecationWarning: Unhandled promise rejections are deprecated. In the future, promise rejections that are not handled will terminate the Node.js process with a non-zero exit code.\r\n```\r\nA similar message appears in the browser console on Ember Twiddle.",
