    "body": "Hello! I'm not sure if this is the right place for this but I wasn't sure where to ask. In the [current documentation for the each template helper](https://emberjs.com/api/ember/3.2/classes/Ember.Templates.helpers/methods/each?anchor=each) it talks about specifying keys but makes no mention of the special values for key, namely: \r\n\r\n@index - The index of the item in the array.\r\n@item - The item in the array itself. This can only be used for arrays of strings or numbers.\r\n@guid - Generate a unique identifier for each object (uses Ember.guidFor). \r\n\r\nWhich I discovered in this [comment](https://discuss.emberjs.com/t/new-glimmer-consideration-each-key/8128/9)\r\n\r\nAre these special values actually still valid in 3.2? And if they are, is it alright if I write them back into the documentation?",
