    "body": "This will likely have to start out as a deprecation (with `until: '2.17.0'`) and then be swapped to an assertion.\r\n\r\nFor the same reason that `init` should always have `_super` called, we should always ensure `_super` is called in `willDestroy` for `FrameworkObject`'s (`Component`, `Route`, `Controller`, `Service`).\r\n\r\nCode for `init` not supering is [here](https://github.com/emberjs/ember.js/blob/e9e2f2b69f625716539b854f4a8934fa945faec8/packages/ember-runtime/lib/system/object.js#L71-L83).",
