    "body": "With the recent deprecation of `baseURL`, we ran into trouble while making the switch.\n\nThe release notes suggest prefixing asset URLs with `/`, but this didn't work when hosting our app with a `rootURL` other than `/`. We had to prepend `rootURL` to all of our asset URLs used in our templates.\n\nEven after this changes, we can't seem to find any documentation which validates what we have done.\n\nThe guides should have some simple workflow which describes when to throw images in your repo, and how you might use them from: within templates, css, etc --- while also describing how this might differ if the `rootURL` is changed.\n",
